## Supabase Query Patterns

**Do:**
```typescript
// Use maybeSingle() when "not found" is expected
const { data: event } = await supabase
  .from('calendar_events')
  .select('id')
  .eq('external_id', eventId)
  .eq('user_id', userId)
  .maybeSingle();  // Returns null if not found

// Explicit column selection
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('deals')
  .select('id, name, value, stage_id');
```

**Don't:**
```typescript
// Don't use single() when record might not exist
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('events')
  .select('*')
  .eq('id', id)
  .single();  // Throws PGRST116 if not found

// Don't use select('*') in edge functions
const { data } = await supabase.from('deals').select('*');  // BAD
```

